When calling stored procedure returning multiple result sets, I am getting this error from MySQL,

   ROCEDURE get_all_by_username can't return a result set in the given context

MySQL needs flag CLIENT_MULTI_RESULTS but there is no way to set this flag in DBDParam. I added following change to apr_dbd_mysql.c so it takes any number value to solve my problem,


    if (fields[6].value != NULL) {
        if (!strcmp(fields[6].value, "CLIENT_FOUND_ROWS"))
           flags |= CLIENT_FOUND_ROWS; /* only option we know */
        else
           flags |= atol(fields[6].value);
    }

Can someone add this feature in the driver?
